  "body": "## üéâ Description\r\n\r\n<!-- Briefly describe the issue you are experiencing (or the feature you want to see added to OpenZeppelin). Tell us what you were trying to do and what happened instead. **Remember, this is _not_ a place to ask for help debugging code; for that, we welcome you in the [OpenZeppelin Slack Channel](https://slack.openzeppelin.org/).** -->\r\n\r\nRight now, many variables are publicly accessible, which could raise issues in some inheritance patterns, for instance if some required checks are not properly enforced by derived contracts. It would be safer to encapsulate the variables and provide setters and getters for clients to use. This issue is meant to foster discussion on this topic, to eventually converge on a unified proposal on how to deal with this. \r\n\r\n\r\n- [ ] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [x] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n",
